{
  "doc_id": "27505",
  "text": "It is critical to investigate students' perceptions of their learning environments, especially in higher education, given the limited research in this sector. While many teachers might believe that developing students' innovation competence is relevant, they could lack the know-how to do so [CITATION_1] . Research on learning environments has also demonstrated a link between students' perceptions of the learning environment and their learning outcomes, with students' perceptions predicting an appreciable amount of variance in outcomes [CITATION_2] ). Therefore, investigating students' perceptions of the learning environment is a valid way to improve learning outcomes [CITATION_3] .",
